<br>
Rangers - The ranger class shouldn't even exist IMO.  The druid class should start out similar to rangers and GROW in power to encompass their druid abilites.  Or perhaps the other way around.  That would more justify the reason that rangers just don't last very long at higher levels.  BUT, they would have backup responsibilities that would offset that.<br>
<br>
Necros, Enchanters, Mages - NONE of these classes should exist.  The true roleplaying wizard would encompass ALL of these abilites.  Raising the dead, Conjuring pets and weapons, charming, etc.  Trying to split it all up and make them balance each other has been a TOTAL disaster.  The problem is, the major abilities have been farmed out to these classes to the point where Wizards really don't exist except as taxi drivers.<br>
<br>
Clerics - Yeah, that works fine.  Heck, the entire GAME centers around that.  Almost TOO much.<br>
<br>
Bards - Adds character.  I think the bard class has been developed quite nicely.<br>
<br>
Monks, Warriors, Rogues - Technically, an expert in combat would be proficient at all of these skills.  But the seperation here is not nearly so bad.  These classes have been developed fairly well, in fact almost TOO well.<br>
<br>
Sk and Pali - The light and dark side of this coin is an intriguing prospect.  However, overall, both classes could be left out.  In the 50+ game, their special abilities are ONLY used in VERY rare circumstances.  Not your standard adventuring group.<br>
<br>
Shaman - Eh.  Great idea, but nothing that couldn't be encompassed by the Dru/Ranger that SHOULD be there.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
The point is, Verant has tried TOO hard to create individualistic classes that they have diluted some of the class abilities to the point that they are virtually useless except for EXTREME circumstances.  It is almost like they tried TOO hard, messed up, and aren't willing to own up to it.  And we basically all suffer.<br>
<br>
W.F. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umarktodd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MarkTodd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/8/01 9:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yes Armok</span><hr size=1> Wraithwave, I totally agree with you on your assessment of the class designs. It seems it was most important for them to print &quot;12 playable classes&quot; on the box...unfortunately, some are WAY more playable than others. And now they are foolish enough to introduce a new class...I'm just waiting for the other pet classes to start screaming. <p>Merkus Stormcrow (40, High Elf, Mostly Retired Wizard)
